# SEO & Performance Guidelines

## Metadata & Structured Data
- Use Next.js metadata where applicable in page files.
- Generate structured data (JSON-LD) using:
  - [src/lib/jsonld.ts](mdc:src/lib/jsonld.ts)
  - [src/app/jsonld.tsx](mdc:src/app/jsonld.tsx)

## Images & Assets
- Optimize images placed under [public/](mdc:public); prefer modern formats when possible.
- Provide `alt` text and dimensions to prevent layout shifts.

## Performance
- Keep components lightweight; avoid unnecessary client components.
- Use streaming/SSR defaults of App Router where appropriate.
- Defer non-critical JS and use `dynamic()` with `ssr: false` only when necessary.

## Internationalization SEO
- Provide canonical and `alternate` language links for `/en` and `/zh` pages.
- Keep identical content synchronized across locales to avoid duplication issues.
- Use proper hreflang attributes in metadata for language alternates.

